Choose Condition ①: BE∥AF
1. Since AB∥CD and AB is not a subset of the plane PCD, then AB∥the plane PCD;
2. The intersection of plane ABEF and plane PCD is EF, so AB∥EF;
3. Moreover, BE∥AF, so the quadrilateral ABEF is a parallelogram, thus AB=EF;
4. Since AB=1 and CD=2, AB=1/2CD, so EF=1/2CD;
5. Because EF∥CD, EF is the median line of △PCD, so F is the midpoint of PD.

